title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that calculates waiting list totals for each municipality. The plan must filter the waiting list data for the month “2025-05” first. We want two values computed. The total per waiting list type and the overall total for the municipality. The output must be sorted in descending order by the municipality’s total. Output in textfile.

operations.table: (SELECT organisation_id, total, waiting_list_type, year_month FROM factwaitinglists) as X
(SELECT organisation_id, municipality FROM organisation) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val total = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val waitingType = r.getField(2).toString; val municip = r.getField(3).toString; (municip, waitingType, total) }
(a: (String, String, Int), b: (String, String, Int)) => (a._1, a._2, a._3 + b._3)
(a: (String, String, Int), b: (String, String, Int)) => (a._1, a._2, a._3 + b._3)

(t: ((String, String, Int), (String, String, Int))) => { val municipality = t._1._1; val type1 = t._2._2; val total1 = t._2._3; val overall = t._1._3; s"${municipality} | ${type1} | ${total1} | ${overall}" }

log.thoughts: I created a plan that filters the waiting list data for 2025-05, joins with organisation to retrieve municipality, computes per-type and municipality totals, attaches the municipality total to each per-type row, sorts by municipality total in descending order, and outputs the results to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT moveout_id FROM (SELECT * FROM factwaitinglists) as X) as X
(SELECT organisation_id, total, waiting_list_type, year_month FROM (SELECT organisation_id, total, waiting_list_type, year_month FROM factwaitinglists) as X) as X
(SELECT organisation_id, municipality FROM (SELECT organisation_id, municipality FROM organisation) as X) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val total = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val waitingType = r.getField(2).toString; val municip = r.getField(3).toString; (municip, waitingType, total) }
(a: (String, String, Int), b: (String, String, Int)) => (a._1, a._2, a._3 + b._3)
(a: (String, String, Int), b: (String, String, Int)) => (a._1, a._2, a._3 + b._3)

(t: ((String, String, Int), (String, String, Int))) => { val municipality = t._1._1; val type1 = t._2._2; val total1 = t._2._3; val overall = t._1._3; s"${municipality} | ${type1} | ${total1} | ${overall}" }
